.TH "lpfc_board_mode_store" 9 "lpfc_board_mode_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_board_mode_store \- Puts the hba in online, offline, warm or error state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" lpfc_board_mode_store
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
class device that is converted into a Scsi_host.
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute, not used.
.IP "buf" 12
containing one of the strings "online", "offline", "warm" or "error".
.IP "count" 12
unused variable.
.SH "RETURN"
-EACCES if enable hba reset not enabled
-EINVAL if the buffer does not contain a valid string (see above)
-EIO if \fBlpfc_workq_post_event\fP or \fBlpfc_do_offline\fP fails
buf length greater than zero indicates success
